public class GameState extends Object implements Serializable
Class GameState

Represents the full state of an ongoing UNO game. This class is used for saving and restoring the game's progress, making it possible to resume gameplay from a previously serialized state.

It contains all relevant components of the game, including:

  • The current Deck
  • The main GameUno instance containing game logic
  • The current state of the Table
  • The Player instances for both the human and the machine

This class implements Serializable, allowing it to be persisted to a file using serialization.
